---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Ahmed Omrane — AI-native builder owning the business → product → engineering arc end-to-end. France-based, European focus, contract engagements only.">
  <div class="page">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <header class="page-header">
        <p class="label">About</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">Ahmed Omrane</h1>
      </header>

      <div class="bio">
        <p>
          I build at the seam where business model, product, and engineering meet — the decisions where getting it wrong is expensive and getting it right compounds.
        </p>
        <p>The work moves through three layers in sequence:</p>
        <ul class="layers">
          <li><strong>Business first:</strong> vision, GTM, the call on what is actually being built and why.</li>
          <li><strong>Product next:</strong> roadmap, prioritisation, sequencing the trade-offs that decide what ships in which quarter.</li>
          <li><strong>Engineering last:</strong> architecture, technical trade-offs, the execution that turns the prior layers into shipped software.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>I own that arc end-to-end.</p>
        <p>
          AI-native execution is how the arc gets delivered solo at senior scope. I run an orchestration layer of agents that does the work of three people while I keep judgement, taste, and trust in the room — not as a productivity tool, as the system the arc runs through. Complex transformations, infrastructure migrations, SaaS transitions: one operator, at a trade-off resolution that previously required a full-stack hire across business, product, and engineering. The seven operating principles behind the orchestration are written up in <a href="/en/writing/orchestration-principles-that-outlive-the-model">Agentic AI Orchestration — 7 Operating Principles</a>.
        </p>

        <p class="label proof-label">Selected proof</p>
        <ul class="proof">
          <li>
            Vendor lock-in exit to a proprietary transport management system at <strong>Enakl</strong> (VC-backed seed, B2B/B2G mobility platform, emerging markets) — built from scratch, 10× operational scaling, zero downtime during full migration. Team of 3: mobile, full-stack Node.js, cloud AWS. Full case file: <a href="/en/work/breaking-vendor-lock-in">Breaking Vendor Lock-In</a> · <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cc4HTB_iRDs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Product demo</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Full SaaS transformation at <strong>Enakl</strong> — multi-tenant architecture, high availability, enterprise-grade security, revenue model shifting from service delivery to software. Team of 5 engineers plus AI coding agents. Full case file: <a href="/en/work/saas-hardening">SaaS Hardening</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Data and analytics infrastructure from scratch at <strong>The Fabulous</strong> (bootstrapped consumer wellness app, 20M+ daily active users) — attribution, growth metrics, and reliable measurement enabling aggressive spend. Team of 5: data science, data analysis, analytics engineering. Architecture deep-dive: <a href="https://medium.com/@ahmedomrane/on-data-analytics-architecture-how-to-design-you-data-model-for-scalable-accurate-analytics-dbt-dcfb7f379c75" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">On Data Analytics Architecture</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          France-based, European market focus, international operating background. I work on contract, fractional, advisory, and partnership engagements — not full-time employment. The shape varies; the constants are end-to-end ownership across business, product, and engineering, with AI-native execution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page {
    padding: var(--space-lg) 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .page-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-content);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-lg);
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .label {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    display: block;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--size-2xl);
  }

  .bio {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .bio p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .bio p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .bio a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .bio a:hover {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .proof-label {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .bio ul.proof {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
  }

  .bio ul.proof li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border);
  }

  .bio ul.proof li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .bio ul.layers {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
  }

  .bio ul.layers li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .bio ul.layers li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .bio ul.layers li strong {
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-inner {
      padding: 0 var(--space-md);
    }
  }
</style>
